          "label": "Key trade-offs or decisions are framed in clean, comparative terms rather than hedged explanations"
        },
        {
          "id": "conversational_not_formal",
          "label": "Reads as someone actually talking to colleagues, not issuing a formal notice"
        }
      ],
      "priority": 4
    },
    {
      "name": "Lean Information Density",
      "category": "Content",
      "description": "Timelines and action items should read as a sequence of checkpoints \u2014 dates and milestones only. Strip role descriptions, process explanations, and details the audience already knows. Anything that doesn't sharpen clarity is noise that dilutes the signal.",
